01:06:43.276 --> 01:06:44.999
outlet. The outlet for adult science fiction was available in the magazines, which we've just been talking about, and 
which have played such an important part in the development of your genre. And the depressing thing is that when writers

01:06:58.508 --> 01:07:12.346
can get the adult audience, especially if it's the adult male audience, that is what they'll go for, and leave 
second-rateers to fall back on writing for children. I say especially in adult male audience because we might compare

01:07:13.728 --> 01:07:24.803
the situation in children's literature of science fiction with that of the historical novel, the straight historical 
novel. You remember that the historical novel was disqualified in the same way that SF set in the future was

01:07:26.167 --> 01:07:34.381
disqualified from consideration as true to life. And you remember further that the genres pushed out into the popular 
literature category got market typed. Well, it seems clear to me that science fiction got market typed as male and the

01:07:43.097 --> 01:07:50.790
historical novel got market typed as female. The readership of science fiction is, I think, still largely male, and 
that of the historical novel is females and children. The historical novel has in fact flourished much more in

01:08:01.444 --> 01:08:08.458
children's literature than has, until recently, science fiction. And that clearly shows, I think, that when a genre is 
relegated to women and children readers, writers would assume right for children as for women. But where they have an

01:08:18.694 --> 01:08:27.409
opportunity to write for a male adult audience, they will take it more readily and not entertain the possibility of 
writing for children. And I suspect, though I might again be corrected that the The slow trickle of women writers into

01:08:32.148 --> 01:08:39.140
the field of science fiction has increased the chances of science fiction getting written for children. Since that's 
another amiable feature of the influence of sex stereotypes on reading habits, that it's assumed that women will want

01:08:39.821 --> 01:08:47.575
to write for children.

01:08:50.272 --> 01:09:02.108
