which I cited earlier, I have come across some ones that I think are very good. And one of the features which makes books

01:09:02.128 --> 01:09:13.123
less than first-rate, I think, is the assumption that issues must be simplified for children. And one side effect of 
this is that you tend to get very clear statements of the going themes and perhaps prejudices in books for children,

01:09:14.285 --> 01:09:27.561
which is in often itself to make them interesting reading. So I thought that it would be of some interest to compare in 
some detail two children's books, which both seem to me to be very good, though not at the first rank, one of which is

01:09:41.707 --> 01:09:47.395
science fiction, nor not purely science fiction, and the other, historical fantasy. Both of these are described as 
mixtures, incidentally, in their blurbs. The science fiction book is described as a mixture of science fiction and

